text: Francis Joseph "Frank" McKenna, (born January 19, 1948) is a Canadian businessman and former politician and diplomat. He is the Deputy Chairman of the Toronto-Dominion Bank. He was the Canadian Ambassador to the United States from 2005 to 2006. He was the 27th Premier of New Brunswick from 1987 to 1997. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:Premiers of New Brunswick Category:Ambassadors of Canada Category:Privy Councillors (Canada) Category:Canadian King's Counsel
